Xiaomi Mi Note 10 Lite (toco) 
Firmware: EEA V13.0.6.0.SFNEUXM
MIUI Optimizations OFF!

## Tips!

I recommend you to disable MIUI optimizations. How?
1. Open settings & open "About Phone"
2. Tap Spam the "MIUI Version"
3. Go back to settings, scroll down to "Additional settings" and open developer options
4. On developer options scroll all way down to the bottom. Now spam the "Reset to default values" option and you will see MIUI optimizations appear by magic.
5. Turn it off & reboot your phone!



If you uninstall the security app you won't be able to see battery stats, it's fine because xiaomi battery stats are shit anyways. 
Replace it with battery Guru Stats from PlayStore.
If you going to use Guru Battery Stats and want to give all permissions you need a Mi account connected so you can toggle on USB debugging (Security Settings) 
in developer options!



You can replace most of the applications with apps from Playstore or F-droid.
1. For Gallery i use https://f-droid.org/packages/com.simplemobiletools.gallery.pro/
2. For file manager i use https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.marc.files&gl=US that is basically a shortcut apk to open the legacy file manager.
3. If you want to see all settings options you can use https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=rk.android.app.shortcutmaker&gl=US i use this one to see
services running in the background mostly. Here's a link how you can create a shortcut for such thing: https://forum.xda-developers.com/t/there-is-a-way-to-check-running-services-and-cached-processes.4354501/post-87751199



